    "summary": "Illustrates the step-by-step process of integrating a frontend application with a blockchain network, covering wallet connection, transaction creation, sig",
    "whatItShows": "This flowchart details the user journey and system interactions for a blockchain transaction. It begins with a frontend request, checks for wallet connectivity (e.g., MetaMask), guides the user through connecting if necessary, then proceeds to create, sign, and send the transaction to the blockchain network for smart contract execution. It also covers the handling of transaction outcomes, updating the UI on success and showing errors on failure.",
